properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 29 at 8:33AM PST until January 29 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 50 mph.
Strongest near Montecito Hills.

* WHERE...Santa Barbara County Mountains.

* WHEN...Until 10 PM PST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways 101 and 154 will be affected with
the strongest winds in the Montecito Hills, San Marcos Pass,
and Gaviota/Refugio areas.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST THIS EVENING... ...HIGH WIND WARNING IS CANCELLED
